The paper deals with the complexity of various problems related to the Federated Byzantine Agreement System (FBAS), which is a distributed consensus protocol used in blockchain technology. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The analysis of the complexity of the problems involves parametrized complexity, which is a topic in Learning and Game Theory (cs.LG) and Graph Theory (cs.GT).
